search_results.snippet: BIOGRAPHY. JUNO Award Nominees, Rum Ragged, take a bold approach to the distinct folk music of their home, the Eastern Canadian island of Newfoundland.

search_results.title: Rum Ragged
search_results.snippet: Rum Ragged are a Canadian folk music group from Newfoundland and Labrador. [1] They are most noted for their 2020 album The Thing About Fish.

search_results.title: Rum Ragged
search_results.snippet: Formed by Aaron Collis and Mark Manning, Rum Ragged takes a bold approach to the distinct folk music of their home, the Eastern Canadian island of Newfoundland.
